second cut
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:a second attempt at shearing an area of wool from a sheep.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes:
Citations
Date: 18/9/1875
Source: Otago Witness
Author:
Vol / Page: 18
Edition:
Quote: No good shearer makes second cuts; the fact that the wool has been left by the first cut proves that the shears have not been handled properly, and the wool thus removed by a second cut is perfectly useless, entails a loss on the manufacturer, and lowers the brand in the market.
Notes:

